          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors.  The purpose of this work is to",
                "investigate the properties of hot, fast rotating",
                "compound nuclei around 32-S and to extract  information",
                "on the Giant Dipole Resonance (GDR) built on excited",
                "states in those systems as a function of the  effective",
                "nuclear temperature.  We have chosen the 32-S as a",
                "compound nucleus in which we have populated the GDR  by",
                "the isospin t = 0 entrance channel.  The attempt to",
                "take advantage of the isovector nature of electric",
                "dipole radiation in order to extract the degree of",
                "isospin mixing in 32-S at high excitation is discussed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "INTAD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Spectra at three angles =60, 90 and 120 degrees",
                "have been normalized to the summed multiplicity (larger",
                "than 2) of low-energy gamma-rays measured by the",
                "multiplicity filter and then transformed to the",
                "compound nucleus center-of-mass frame."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
